NAKAMURA\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"more modern image\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"display\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1673}, {\"ngram\": \"her biggest hits\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"Nakamura's performance\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1855}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest cheers\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1918}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"bars\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2075}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Supporters said she represented the vibrancy of modern-day France while her detractors said her music owes more to foreign influence than French and that her colloquial use of the French language was unfitting.Dancers and flame bearers took to the roofs of Paris as rain fell.\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2157, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995073740262935, \"rank\": 0.0004915505902505328, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2236, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9875993720081407, \"rank\": 0.011774041677950063, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2278, \"end\": 2293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999988275033099, \"rank\": 1.172313450346177e-06, \"text\": \"French language\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2355, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999704241689, \"rank\": 2.9575839207639987e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Supporters\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2108}, {\"ngram\": \"the vibrancy\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"her detractors\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2184}, {\"ngram\": \"her music\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2199}, {\"ngram\": \"foreign influence\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"her colloquial use\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2270}, {\"ngram\": \"Dancers\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2315}, {\"ngram\": \"flame bearers\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2333}, {\"ngram\": \"the roofs\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2351}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2368}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The rain will not stop me from cheering on the Olympics - sport is everything to me and I'd do whatever it takes to watch this,\\\" said Flavia Merluzzi, 20, an architecture student.Amid rumours that Canadian singer Celine Dion could also be part of the show, spectator Chantal Beauvais said it would be \\\"magical\\\" to watch her.The ceremony featured other recorded footage, including rhythmic sounds of stone chisels and wood saws to images of the restoration of Notre-Dame after the fire in 2019Many details have been kept secret, including who will be the last to carry the torch and light the Olympic cauldron to mark the start of the Games.\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 3015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2572, \"end\": 2580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9923099773482839, \"rank\": 0.0044658589763672055, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"scor