ernational backdrop.\", \"from\": 8108, \"to\": 8444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8346, \"end\": 8353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9988974476271942, \"rank\": 0.0011037661793753578, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 8385, \"end\": 8392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9155900213402516, \"rank\": 0.08887048522240555, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 8397, \"end\": 8401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\", \"score\": 0.9726123306796914, \"rank\": 0.028157451500940588, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Armed police\", \"from\": 8108, \"to\": 8120}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 8137, \"to\": 8146}, {\"ngram\": \"inflatable boats\", \"from\": 8150, \"to\": 8166}, {\"ngram\": \"the armada\", \"from\": 8170, \"to\": 8180}, {\"ngram\": \"its passage\", \"from\": 8186, \"to\": 8197}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine\", \"from\": 8204, \"to\": 8213}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 8221, \"to\": 8235}, {\"ngram\": \"an opening ceremony\", \"from\": 8241, \"to\": 8260}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 8271, \"to\": 8276}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 8285, \"to\": 8294}, {\"ngram\": \"the last Games\", \"from\": 8301, \"to\": 8315}, {\"ngram\": \"the Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 8318, \"to\": 8337}, {\"ngram\": \"2022 - wars\", \"from\": 8357, \"to\": 8368}, {\"ngram\": \"a tense international backdrop\", \"from\": 8413, \"to\": 8443}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France is at its highest level of security, though officials have repeatedly said there is no specific threat to the opening ceremony or the Games.Israeli competitors are being escorted by elite tactical units to and from events and given 24-hour protection throughout the Olympics due to the war in Gaza, officials say.Scores of world leaders are in Paris for the opening ceremony, which will also be protected by snipers on rooftops.\", \"from\": 8445, \"to\": 8880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8445, \"end\": 8451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9545549878554529, \"rank\": 0.02233397906873155, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 8745, \"end\": 8749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\", \"score\": 0.9726123306796914, \"rank\": 0.028157451500940588, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\"}, {\"begin\": 8796, \"end\": 8801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999973171043, \"rank\": 2.682872618341574e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its highest level\", \"from\": 8458, \"to\": 8475}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 8479, \"to\": 8487}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 8496, \"to\": 8505}, {\"ngram\": \"no specific threat\", \"from\": 8536, \"to\": 8554}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 8558, \"to\": 8578}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 8582, \"to\": 8591}, {\"ngram\": \"Israeli competitors\", \"from\": 8592, \"to\": 8611}, {\"ngram\": \"elite tactical units\", \"from\": 8634, \"to\": 8654}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 8667, \"to\": 8673}, {\"ngram\": \"24-hour protection\", \"from\": 8684, \"to\": 8702}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 8714, \"to\": 8726}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 8734, \"to\": 8741}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 8751, \"to\": 8760}, {\"ngram\": \"Scores\", \"from\": 8765, \"to\": 8771}, {\"ngram\": \"world leaders\", \"from\": 8775, \"to\": 8788}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 8806, \"to\": 8826}, {\"ngram\": \"snipers\", \"from\": 8860, \"to\": 8867}, {\"ngram\": \"rooftops\", \"from\": 8871, \"to\": 8879}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine's riverbed has been swept for bombs, and Paris' airspace is closed.For the Games more generally, radar-surveillance planes and Reaper drones will monitor sensitive sites from above, and Mirage 2000 fighter jets will be on standby to intercept aircraft straying into restricted airspace.French President Emmanuel Macron, who won a second mandate two years ago, had hoped the Olympics would cement his legacy.\", \"from\": 8881, \"to\": 9298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8885, \"end\": 8890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999995459348, \"rank\": 4.3611478124555497e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 8932, \"end\": 8937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.712211930345536e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 9077, \"end\": 9088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dassault_Mirage_2000\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mirage 2000\", \"types\": [\"Q11436\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dassault_Mirage_2000\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dassault_Mirage_2000\"}, {\"begin\": 9194, \"end\": 9209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\