: 22830, \"to\": 22850}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 22854, \"to\": 22863}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Games\", \"from\": 22876, \"to\": 22892}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French soccer superstar Zinedine Zidane was shown running across Paris to bring the flame, in a pre-recorded video that included him taking it onto the metro.Spectators were treated to more postcard-like depictions of France as a huge cancan line performed by Moulin Rouge cabaret dancers on the banks.\", \"from\": 22896, \"to\": 23198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22896, \"end\": 22902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.8027420341907863, \"rank\": 0.1760302864968706, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 22920, \"end\": 22935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 22961, \"end\": 22966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999606644, \"rank\": 3.937208518829513e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 23114, \"end\": 23120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7655003378157308, \"rank\": 0.3063142235500324, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 23156, \"end\": 23168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.297336058376839e-22, \"text\": \"Moulin Rouge\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the flame\", \"from\": 22976, \"to\": 22985}, {\"ngram\": \"a pre-recorded video\", \"from\": 22990, \"to\": 23010}, {\"ngram\": \"the metro\", \"from\": 23044, \"to\": 23053}, {\"ngram\": \"Spectators\", \"from\": 23054, \"to\": 23064}, {\"ngram\": \"more postcard-like depictions\", \"from\": 23081, \"to\": 23110}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge cancan line\", \"from\": 23124, \"to\": 23142}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 23188, \"to\": 23197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are super excited, it happens once in a lifetime,\\\" 17-year-old Elise Boukorrass said before the show.AYA NAKAMURA SINGSA more modern image of France was on display when French-Malian singer Aya Nakamura sang some of her biggest hits, as well as one by beloved crooner Charles Aznavour, accompanied by the French army choir.Nakamura's performance drew some of the biggest cheers so far from those by the river and watching the ceremony in bars.She is the most-listened-to French female singer in the world but when it first emerged she might perform it sparked a row over French identity.\", \"from\": 23198, \"to\": 23789, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23344, \"end\": 23350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995073740262935, \"rank\": 0.0004915505902505328, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 23392, \"end\": 23404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}, {\"begin\": 234